fields.description:
Discovered while investigating GUI-2174.  Configuring 'testlogs' or 'test-logs' as the ELB access logs prefix works, but logs collection fails when the prefix has an uppercase char (e.g.'Test-Logs').

Per [~spark]'s comment in GUI-2174...

{code}
When enabling access logs via console, if I don't specify a bucket prefix, the console auto-generates ELB-AccessLogs-{ELB_NAME} as the prefix (which is a bug tracked in GUI-2173). Then strangely, object storage service throws <403 Forbidden> when this prefix is used.
{code}

We didn't observe this error in August when implementing GUI-1622 in the console, so marking this as a regression.
